===Etymology===
Used by {{w|Alfred Hitchcock}}, as an arbitrary Scottish surname. The actual name comes from {{w|Ulster}}: {{af|en|Mc-|t1=son of|dubh|t2=black|lang2=ga|Fionn|lang3=ga|lit3=fairheaded}}.<ref>{{cite-web|entry=Mag DHUIBHFINN|work=Irish Names and Surnames|url=http://www.libraryireland.com/names/mag/mag-dhuibhfinn.php}}</ref>
See also Wikipedia's {{w|MacGuffin#History_and_use|''MacGuffin § History and use''}}.

